text.tspan: Weekly confirmed cases of influenza A H1N1 (2009), sentinel
Sentinel surveillance consists of data routinely collected from sites representative of the country's population. Only a
fraction of potential cases of influenza are tested by labs to confirm whether they have influenza and to identify their strain.
The level of testing may vary between countries and over time. This shows the number of cases that were confirmed to
have a strain of influenza A virus related to the H1N1 ("Swine flu") pandemic that emerged in 2009.
Data source: FluNet by the World Health Organization (2023)
